African Union Commission chairperson Moussa Faki Mahamat is today expected to preside over the National Elections Conference at the KICC in Nairobi. President Uhuru Kenyatta is expected to welcome Mahamat to address the conference, organised by the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission, the Kura Yangu Haki Yangu Initiative and other stakeholders. NASA presidential flagbearer Raila Odinga is also expected to address the event, whose theme is &ldquo;Working together towards a credible and peaceful General Election, 2017&rdquo;.According to a programme released by the IEBC yesterday, the country&rsquo;s top leadership will reaffirm its commitment in ensuring that the forthcoming polls are credible and peaceful. &ldquo;One of the guiding questions is on our responsibility and commitment in ensuring peaceful and credible elections,&rdquo; reads the programme.Among the guests who will address the conference include Terry Tselane (vice chairperson of the Independent Electoral Commission of South Africa), Robert Godec (US ambassador) and Ambassador Sahle-Work Zewde (director general of UNON).IEBC chairperson Wafula Chebukati,Eliud Wabukala (EACC), Chief Justice David Maraga, former Vice President Moody Awori, Cotu secretary general Francis Atwoli, Political Parties Dispute Tribunal chairperson Kyalo Mbobu, Registrar of Political Parties Lucy Ndungu and DPP Keriako Tobiko will also attend the event. Yesterday, the pre-conference activities included exhibitions.